commit 061c5941c226234c5064489010d8345a35bca78e
Author: Gustaf Neumann <neumann@wu-wien.ac.at>
Date:   2025-03-25

    Add percent-decoding support to relayhost parsing
    
    - Provide an error message, when URL provided via "relayhost" is invalid
    
    - If the provided URL contains userinfo, decode it and split it at the
      colon; if the colon is missing, log a warning and do not configure
      user credentials.
    
    - Introduce a new helper function, PercentDecode(), to decode
      percent-encoded characters from the relayhost userinfo string.  This
      is currently a duplication of the NaviServer function, since
      NaviServer does not provide a public API for this.

M	nssmtpd.c

