commit c4539044078110b0198d319d767a06d59981fc07
Author: Gustaf Neumann <neumann@wu-wien.ac.at>
Date:   2025-03-23

    Enhanced SMTP relay support and improve multi-line response processing
    
    - Implement SmtpdAuthPlainCommand to support AUTH PLAIN authentication
      One can specify now "plain://USER:PWF@MAILHOST:587" for the "relay"
      parameter in the configuration section
    
    - This change required using the Ns_ParseUrl() API function from
      NaviServer and to introduce new configuration fields for relay
      authentication (relayuser and relaypassword).
    
    - General code cleanups and error-handling enhancements for robust
        SMTP relay communication.
    
      * Refactor multi-line response processing by adding
        SmtpdReadMultiLine and SmtpdJoinMultiLine functions to handle
        enhanced status codes (e.g. "535-5.7.8") and strip CRLF/newline
        delimiters.
    
      * Change connection ID type from unsigned int to uintptr_t for
        better portability and long running servers.
    
      * Improved logging messages
    
      * Provide compatibility with the latests NaviServer 5 and 4.99 versions.
    
      * Improved error handling and error messages to distinguish between
        timeouts and other errors, This required adding further output
        parameters to functions to pass Ns_ReturnCode pointers.
    
    - Bump SMTPD version from "2.3" to "2.4".

M	nssmtpd.c

